entries.femaleVariant: Valerie, right? I'm Angel, your Angel.
entries.maleVariant: Vincent, right? I'm Angel, your Angel.

entries.femaleVariant: Busy day, huh? Here, take a load off. Think I've got just the thing to help you relax.
But we'll get to know each other well in no time, honey.
It's V. Just V. Only people I know real well get to use my real name.
Afterlife.
You gotta help me. Please…
I'm no threat, and she could be in trouble. Just wanna talk to her, find out if she's OK.
Look, I barely knew her. And I have no clue where she is.
Nobody came lookin' for her? Nothin' out of the ordinary happen?
You interrupted the session…
Did I do something wrong? Were you not satisfied...?
I need this info. Name your price.
She's not here, and I barely even knew her. That's all I can say.
It'll be worth your while. Try to remember.
I'll pay you.
Need your help, please.
Answer the question.
Answer the question. Do it. And then you can get back to whatever it is you do.
How about those good looks of yours? Be a shame if they dipped below club standards…
Wonder what happens to a doll that suddenly goes ugly…
There was an... incident... with a client.
Tom might know. He and Evelyn were close... Go ask him. And please leave me alone.
Who's Tom?
Tell me about this "incident"?
Tom – who's he?
Friend of Evelyn's. Wasn't a free moment they weren't together.
Where'll I find him?
He's a doll here. Works the VIP area. Booth two.
This incident with the client... what happened?
Then they just buried it. No more questions, not another peep about it, anywhere, from anyone.
Evelyn Parker. Whaddaya know about her?
What do you know about Evelyn?
Not what I expected.
Enlightening conversation, that.
Wait just a sec. That's not how this works. You can't ask me about the dollhouse or anything like that…
I could get in serious trouble. Go, please, just go.
Gotta say, not what I expected. Was hoping for a thrill or two, not a grim, soul-searching debate.
entries.maleVariant: Heh, gotta say, not what I expected. Was hoping for a thrill or two, not a grim, soul-searching debate.

entries.femaleVariant: Had all kinds of things going on in my head lately. This was... different. Refreshing.
Nobody saw, nobody knew, who attacked first, it was all a mystery…
Sheesh. Don't ask for me again. Ever.
Look, baby, I don't decide what happens in here. Your subconscious drives everything.
Next time, remind me to tell my subconscious to go fuck itself.
Um... just don't tell anyone, OK? About this?
Came here to talk to Angel, not an algo parading around as a doll.
Yes. That is what we do at Clouds.
Think I get why people come here, come back. But I came for something else…
What...? What happened?
Listen, I'm looking for someone who worked here – Evelyn Parker. Know her? Know where she is?
You must see the big picture. You focus too much on details, minor ones. Like Evelyn.
What did you mean – "happened"? Know something I don't?
What happened to you. What you keep inside and never reveal, to anyone.
I was told this place'd fulfill my deepest desires. Not what I was expecting, this.
When true desires go unfulfilled, they turn into needs. We are here to reach for them and beyond.
So what's it I need so badly?
To come to terms with the fact that you died once already only to face another kind of death.
And that is...?
Come, now, you know…
Not about to come to terms with shit. The fact I'm dying's an incentive. I'm running from that, livin' it up.
Come to terms… Sure, lemme just curl up here on the floor and wait for... whatever.
You wished to leave something behind. A piece of yourself. That's why this all began.
Wasn't even that long ago...
Yeah, wanted to reach the top, be someone. Still do.
But, seems like that might not happen anymore.
But are you asking the right questions? How can you change what has already happened?
Got only one right question now – the one I asked. Where's Evelyn Parker?
These are questions to which you'll find the answers on your own.
You wished to be remembered.
Still, if I gotta die, I wanna go down in history. Fuck it, even a footnote'd do.
People I've lost live on in my thoughts. And that's what I'll be – a memory.
Think I might just be... afraid. So I imagine these things to distract myself from the thought of... the void.
If what I saw before's any indication, I…
entries.maleVariant: If what I saw before's any indication, wh…

entries.femaleVariant: You are sensitive. That does not make you weak. Try to suppress your emotions... and you'll drown.
Why'd the manager say she doesn't work here anymore? When was she last here? You know anything?
Snuffed it once and I'm gonna have to do it all over again. Got no idea how to stop it. There, happy?
Trusted someone and they fucked me over. The end.
Really rather not talk about it.
That won't make it go away. It's a problem that grows larger every day. You can't ignore it.
I'm... doing something about it, all right?
But you don't expect any good of people.
Hm. Not anymore, I don't.
I'll be shredded. I'll disappear. There'll be... nothing.
You can't know that.
No… but I got a pretty good idea.
No no no no no, please, I've got a kid!
Looking for a woman named Evelyn Parker. Know where she is?
entries.maleVariant: Lookin' for a woman named Evelyn Parker. Know where she is?

entries.femaleVariant: Evelyn...? I don't know, I - I heard she left or… or she had an accident or t-t-then she left, m-maybe she...
Looking for Evelyn Parker.
Where'll I find Woodman?
Who's Tom?
And where do I go to find Woodman? He work here?
He... supervises the dolls. Has an office in a back room, a-all the way up the stairs. No outsiders allowed.
Who's this Tom and where'll I find him?
Tom works here. VIP area. I - I saw him today…
That's it, that's all I know. I've already said too much... Shit, if Woodman finds out...
Samurai.
How'd you know I'm dying?
Of all the voices in your head, the loudest is that calling for help. That's why you're here.
There's something in the mirrors, way back…
Deep inside... you fear this, cower before it.
So what if I do? Why do you care?
entries.maleVariant: So what if I do? Wha... Why do you care?

entries.femaleVariant: It's a projection – your inner landscape.
Just what I needed – therapy with a robohooker.
I'm not going to analyze you. I won't play any tricks.
Where'd all this happen?
Where'd it happen?
In her booth.
Number...?
Eleven.
Give up. That's what you're saying.
I was out to grab everything, and then, well... it all happened. Feels like that person wasn't even me…
And after that? Do you think death is a disappearing act followed by exactly nothing?
Need a straighter answer than that.
Look, I'm not... I - I mean, I wasn't... S-she was friends with Tom, OK? Ask him.
Or Woodman – I mean, Mr. Forrest. He should know.
Relax, I don't usually gab.
Don't you worry, I'll find a way.
We're not supposed to accept anything from clients! Everything goes through the shift bosses, I - I can't just…
Evelyn – tell me what you know or I'll say you asked me to pay you.
Thanks.
I don't know the specifics. One doesn’t ask about these things around here.
Hm, no longer part of the world, you will still have an impact there.
Rather not think that one day it'll all disappear.
I'll be gone, and everything else'll be biz as usual.
entries.maleVariant: That I'll be gone and everything else'll be biz as usual.

entries.femaleVariant: I wonder what I'll feel, what I'll think – if I'll even do either.
Can you picture it?
No. And that's, I guess, why I'm looking for some kind of explanation. They're out there.
So you believe death is not the end, after all. Reassuring.
The thought of it doesn't sadden you?
Not really.
"Sad" is an understatement.
'Course I'm sad. And... surprised. Death was something that happened to other people – hell, that I DEALT to others. Now my number'll be up.
Not any more than rain outside my window or another species going extinct.
Was gonna go out in a memorable way... and later, lots later. Turns out death don't give a shit what you want.
You wished to do so much, thought you had time.
One giant hamster wheel, these last few years. Thought I'd finally catch up, be able to sit back, take a breather…
Well, I am saddened. Saddened to think all your anxiety will be gone... yet you will not be there to enjoy it.
You're gonna help me. Need to get into that booth.
I can. But that's it. Won't answer any more questions. Tom knows something – go bother him.
Please don't act like you know me. I just want some answers.
Yeah, well, best laid plans, yadda, yadda, yadda…
Death is inevitable, this we know. Yet somehow, it always comes as a surprise.
No more grinding my teeth over unfinished biz, dirty glitches in my system or catching a bullet as I walk down an alley. But so what? Yeah.
Or just some stranger's voice in my own body, yappin' away…
Here's what I don't do. Spill to any rando who walks in here.
Now, Evelyn Parker – where is she?
Lookin' for someone.
How do you know what's happening to me?
I'm just looking for someone.
There's something in the mirrors…
How do I get in there?
Is it occupied now?
Booth eleven occupied now?
No, it's been "out of order" since…
Why? What for?
Not your biz. Can you open it or not?
Just... what happened, exactly?
This is what "fulfilling my deepest desires" looks like?
Gonna tell me where Evelyn is?
I died and now I'm dying again. Happy?
Don't wanna talk about it.
I got fucked over.
Need to find out what happened first.
So I should just give up and die?
Doesn't everyone?
Wanted too much at once.
[Lie down] I'll live on in people's minds, their memories.
[Lie down] Death's the end. The very end.
I'm scared of what'll happen to me.
Rather not think it'll all disappear.
[Sit] Fine.
I know that you're dying.
This is the part where I tell you what you must do.
Uh, OK. Be my guest.
You've never backed down from anything, so don't stop now. Not one step backwards.
In this city, people die on their way to the corner store for a scop-pop.
But that threat's never stopped you. You dive into the middle of it all. Always have.
Things're moving way too fast. Around me, without me. I... I can't keep up.
A minor delusion. The truth is, we and our paths are braided, neverending, ever transforming, not being but becoming.
Listen, V. Never look back. If you must kill, kill. If you must burn all the world to the ground, then let it burn. OK?
Actually, I'm saying the opposite.
What now?
So, where do we go from here?
Thanks... for this.
I... I don't wanna go out there.
No one ever does. But eventually we all must.
Calm down.
Quit it with the shakes already.
I beg you…
Gotta ask you a question, so listen close, OK?
Try booth two. He's probably in there.
Look around. Tell me what you see.
My sole aim is to fulfill your greatest need.
And what's happening inside you... it could change the world.
[Touch] Can't keep up with what's happening around me anymore.
Thanks...
Talk straight.
Quit it with the shakes.
Relax.
[Stand] Tell me what you know about Evelyn.
[Stand] I'll pay for info.
[Stand] Need your help. Please.
[Stand] You're good looking. It'd be a shame to lose that.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
Talk or I'll report you.
Anyone 'sides me come around lookin' for her?
You're good looking. It'd be a shame to lose that.
Anyone 'sides me come around lookin' for her?
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
[Safeword] Afterlife.
[Safeword] Samurai.
It's just "V."
Sure, why not. Do what you do best.
I'm done planning for the future.
Don't have to worry about a thing anymore.
No. That's why I'm still looking.
[Open]
